==English==

===Etymology===
From the Middle English, from the Latin ''[[Centaurus]]'' from the Greek ''[[Kentauros]]'' (entered English ca. 14c)

===Noun===
'''Centaur'''

# An icy [[planetoid]] that orbits the Sun between [[Jupiter]] and [[Neptune]]

[[Category: English nouns]]
[[Category: Astronomy]]

# A creature of Greek mythology with a the head of a bull and the body of a man.

